{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"]}],"metadata":{"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset","title":"centerOffset","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"property","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159","fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h"},"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CGVector","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"dx","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the left."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to zero and its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"text":" to half the height of the view.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"title":"MapLibre","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"object that corresponds to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol. When an annotation’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"offscreen.","type":"text"}],"title":"MLNAnnotationView","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotationView"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"title":"MLNAnnotation","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotation"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"title":"centerOffset","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","role":"symbol"}}}